name: Bessie the Muskie-Lake-Serpent
description: Muskellunges are large, aggressive, predatory fish that display a range of interesting behaviors, including sticking their head out of the water and attacking very large prey, including humans. When mating, they can group up and give the appearance of being one long, serpent-like animal. They may be behind a number of local sea serpent sitings in lakes across North America.
